  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 36,
      "text": "And I felt it was my duty to them, and to my parents, to the Jewish race, and to the British people who gave us home, and love, and saved our lives too, and to this wonderful man who saved us, of whom I have said so little so far, and who's a very firm part of my life now, because he only lives down the road.",
      "word_count": 67
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Nicholas Winton.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "He's 87 years old.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And you know, he just took it upon himself to go to Prague and organize the transports.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And he worked tirelessly, on top of his normal job, to find as many homes as possible.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "He was a great organizer.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And I mean, he's been honored by the queen for his services to humanity, because he's not only helped us children, he's not only saved our lives and all our children and all the future generations, he's also a founding member of Abbeyfields, the homes for the ages, and has been, for many years, president of [?",
      "word_count": 57
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Mencap. ?] And he's revered, you know, by so many.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And he's a wonderful, wonderful man.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And so, you know-- and I spend my time now talking, giving talks on my life and on the children transports and on my book.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And each time I give a talk, I feel I am doing something for my parents and for all those who perished.",
      "word_count": 22
    }
  ],
